The '''Noohani''' is one of the [[Baloch people|Baloch]] tribe. They are subnation of Rind Baloch. Noohani mostly live in [[Sindh province]], Pakistan. Their Tribal Chief is Sardar Hakim khan Noohani who is from Kai, a little village near [[Sehwan Sharif]]. Noohani speak the [[Sindhi language|Sindhi]] and [[Balochi language]]s.

Sardar Mohammad Khan Noohani was the chief Sardar of Noohani tribe. He died on 16 August 2015. <ref>[http://www.dawn.com/news/727095/heritage-the-ancient-sites-of-kai-and-naig-valleys Heritage: The ancient sites of Kai and Naig valleys]</ref>

